        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 1:22AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 122 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles southwest of South Texas Botanical
Gardens to 8 miles southwest of Malaquite Beach to 10 miles northeast
of Kenedy County Wind Farms. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Flour Bluff, Corpus Christi Country Club, Packery Channel, South
Texas Botanical Gardens, Chapman Ranch, Cabaniss Field, Corpus
Christi Naval Air Station, Kings Crossing Subdivision, Padre Balli
Park, Bay Area Medical Center, Spohn Hospital South, Driscoll
Childrens Hospital, Malaquite Beach, Texas A&amp;M University Corpus
Christi, Waldron Field, Corpus Christi, and La Palmera Mall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
